 Las Vegas, Nevada – An American monster truck driver called Lee O’Donnell recently performed what’s believed to be the world’s first front-flip in a monster truck. The feat, which took place during the Monster Jam Finals in Las Vegas over the weekend, saw O’Donnell launch his truck into a somersault after mounting the ramp on his back wheels with the vehicle’s nose pointing in the air. Skip to 2m25s in the video above if you’re in a hurry. 